---
---

<section id="faq" class="py-20 sm:py-24 bg-neutral-50">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <span class="inline-block text-academy-teal text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">FAQ</span>
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black text-brand-charcoal mb-4">
        Questions Before You Book
      </h2>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Items -->
    <div class="space-y-4">

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">What are the requirements for enrollment?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          Dogs must be at least 16 weeks old and have their rabies vaccination. All dogs require an in-person assessment with our trainers before being approved for enrollment — unless they have previously completed training at our K9 Academy location.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">Can intact (unspayed/unneutered) dogs attend?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          Intact dogs are only permitted in our Day & Train program, where they receive individualized attention and are managed by our trainers throughout the day. They cannot attend regular daycare.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">How do you keep dogs safe at your facility?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          Safety is our top priority. Every dog is assessed in person before joining. Our staff are highly skilled at reading body language and managing group dynamics — they intervene before any situation can escalate. In 15 years of socializing dogs of every breed and temperament, we have maintained a perfect safety record. It's why we're trusted as the safest daycare in the GTA.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">My dog is nervous around other dogs — can they still attend?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          Absolutely. We specialize in working with nervous dogs. Our staff carefully match them with compatible, calm playmates and manage the introduction process. For nervous dogs, we recommend attending 3–5 days per week during the first few months for consistent exposure and faster confidence building.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">What if my dog gets injured?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          All of our staff are trained and equipped to provide first aid. We also maintain direct contact with nearby emergency veterinary clinics and can respond quickly if a situation ever requires it.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">What training tools do you use?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          For our Day & Train program, we use prong collars, e-collars, slip leads, and muzzles as needed. The e-collar delivers TENS unit-type muscle stimulation — the same technology used by chiropractors — not a shock. These tools are used to establish clear communication and reliable responses in real-world situations.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">Can I tour the facility before enrolling?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          We do not currently offer in-person facility tours, as they can be disruptive to the dogs in our care. However, we are working on a virtual tour that will be available soon. In the meantime, you can see our facility through photos on our website and Instagram.
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
        <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
          <span class="text-base font-semibold text-brand-charcoal pr-4">What are your hours and how often should my dog attend?</span>
          <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-neutral-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19.5 8.25l-7.5 7.5-7.5-7.5" />
          </svg>
        </summary>
        <div class="px-6 pb-6 text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
          We are open Monday through Friday, 7:00 AM to 8:00 PM. For best results — especially for nervous or under-socialized dogs — we recommend 3–5 days per week for at least the first few months.
        </div>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
